Why a baby schedule matters:

A consistent routine helps babies feel secure, improves sleep, supports digestion, and builds trust.

 It also makes it easier for us as parents to tune in and bond deeply with our little ones.

Saving these precious days, one cuddle at a time!

Time | Activity
7:00 AM – Gentle stretching, positive words & greetings
7:30 AM – Diaper-free time + play gym under morning sunlight
9:00 AM – Feeding and short nap
11:30 AM – Coconut oil massage
12:00 PM – Bath time (breast milk for cleansing, no soap!)
12:30 PM – Dressed, fed & off to nap (swaddled or not)
3:00 PM – Diaper change, cuddles & quiet awake time
4:30 PM – Evening walk
5:30 PM – Tummy time & play
6:30 PM – Feeding and short nap
8:00 PM – Night massage with coconut oil
8:30 PM – Change into fresh clothes & sleep sack
9:00 PM – Final feed & bedtime

Day in my life !! 

From discipline to tradition, motherhood has taught me the beauty of balance. 🌸
I wake up early to pour into myself, so I can give the best to my family.
Watching my son grow independent, sharing morning sankalpas, and cherishing everyday moments — it’s all part of a life I once dreamed of.

The gym sharpens my energy, traditions keep me rooted, and friendships make the journey even more beautiful.
From friends to fellow moms — and now, watching our little princesses grow side by side — what a gift this life is. ✨

And just like that… my baby boy had his first graduation. 🧑‍🎓💙
From tiny steps to giant leaps, you’ve grown right before my eyes.
Today isn’t just your graduation — it’s a beautiful reminder of how far we’ve come together.
So proud of you, my little sunshine.
Enjoy each journey and celebrate the little things — because they are the big things. 🌟🎓
